<p>When you use Parliamentary Search, you are searching for records in an index. The records have a summary page you can view. In most cases, you can click through from the summary page to the original digital material.</p>
    
    <p>Records are of several types. Some may have web links, others may not. This reflects the information available at the time of indexing.
</p>

    <p>As information systems have changed, approaches to storing information relating to Parliamentary material have also changed. Different records have different levels of detail. The way sets of records have been indexed has also changed.
</p>

<p>We want to enable you to find the information useful to you in a straightforward way. Improving Parliamentary Search is part of that work - work that we will continue. <strong>Your feedback and comments as a user of Search enable us to plan future work.</strong></p>

<p>
The records you see in Search are created manually. The index is managed manually. 
</p>

<p>
Over time, some web locations have changed: for example, links to Hansard material from the 2005-06 session. You can use the Hansard website to find the full text using the date and column references displayed in Parliamentary Search. </p>


<h2>Early day motions</h2>

<p>Records for early day motions are available from November 1989. Early day motions and their amendments are shown together.</p>

<h2>Legislation </h2>

<h3>Acts and bills </h3>

<p>
Records for acts are available from 1801 and subject indexed from 1987. Records for bills are available from 1987. Records do not include the full text of acts or of bills.</p>


<h3>Delegated legislation </h3>

<p>
Records for statutory instruments are available from May 1992. 
Records do not include the full text of statutory instruments. </p>

<h2>Member contributions: Hansard and grand committees</h2>

<p>For the 1987-88 session, records for contributions are for private notice questions and business statements.</p>

<p>For the 1992-93 session, records for contributions include all proceedings.</p>

<p>From the 1992-93 session to the 2005-06 session, up to eight contributions were incorporated into a single indexed record for House of Commons material. For a Member exceeding eight contributions in a debate, there may be two or more indexed records relating to their contributions in that debate. For House of Lords material, a single indexed record was created for multiple contributions. </p>

<p>Links to contributions in Commons Hansard are available from December 2000.</p>

<p>Links to contributions in Lords Hansard are available from May 2005.</p>

<p>For the 2005-06 session, records for contributions include both Houses.</p>






 

<h2>Parliamentary committees</h2>

<p>
Records may include links, but do not include the full text of reports of proceedings. Records for witnesses providing oral evidence to select committees are available.</p>

<p>Records of committees are available from 1992.</p>

<p>Records for witnesses submitting written evidence are not available after 15th October 2012. 
</p>

<p>Records of Lords select committee oral evidence are available from the 2014-15 session.</p>

<h2>Parliamentary papers</h2> 

<h3>Command papers, House of Commons and House of Lords papers</h3>

<p>Selected records are available from 1800.</p>

<p>Records are available from 1992 and include web links from 2005. The text of Parliamentary papers is not included.</p>




<h3>Deposited papers </h3>

<p>
Records are available from 1987.</p>

<p>Links between deposited papers and the commitment to deposit are available from May 2005. </p>

<p>Deposited papers can be downloaded from 2007 onwards. </p>


<h2>Parliamentary proceedings </h2>


<h3>Chamber business </h3>

<p>Records from the 1987-88 session include private notice questions and business statements.</p>

<p>Records from the 1992-93 session include all published Commons proceedings.</p>

<p>Records of royal assent proceedings are available after 2011. </p>

<p> 
Where a division has taken place, the result is noted in the record of the associated proceeding. 
</p>

<p>Records with web links to Commons Hansard are available from December 2000.</p>

<p>Records with web links to Lords Hansard are available from May 2005.</p>




 
<h3>Written corrections </h3> 


<p>Records of ministerial corrections are available from 2007.</p>

<p>Records of written corrections by members of the House of Commons other than ministers are available from April 2024. </p>


<h2>Parliamentary questions </h2>

<h3>Oral questions </h3>

<p>Indexed references of oral questions in the Commons and Lords are available from the 1987-88 session. </p>

<p>Records of oral questions in the Commons are available with web links from December 2000.</p>

<p>Records of oral questions in the Lords are available with web links from October 2005.</p>

<p>Records of oral questions including full text are available from the 2005-06 session.</p>

<p>Indexed references show that one record was created for lead and first supplementary questions. Single records were created for any subsequent supplementaries.</p>

<p>Some recorded web location links have changed: this includes Hansard material from the 2005-06 session.</p>

<p>From the 2005-06 session, for each question tabled, one combined question and answer record was created. If questions were grouped and answered with a single answer by a Minister, the answer text was replicated in a record for each question.</p>

<p>From 1st April 2012 a record is created for each answer. </p>

<p>From September 2013 until the end of the 2013-14 session, title links to Commons oral questions which are not yet answered are shown in grey text: the title is updated with a link to Hansard after the question is answered.</p>



<h3>Written questions </h3>

<p>"Indexed references" refers to records created manually.</p>

<h4>Commons written questions</h4>

<p>Records of written questions in the Commons show indexed references from the 1987-88 session. </p>

<p>Records of written questions in the Commons show full text from the 1996-97 session.</p>

<p>Records of written questions in the Commons show web links from December 2000. </p>

<p>Before the 2005-06 session, written questions from the same member were grouped and answered together by a minister and were shown as a single question.</p>

<p>Publication of Commons written answers ceased in Hansard from 12th September 2014.</p>

<h4>Lords written questions</h4>

<p>
Records for Lords Members declaring an interest which may be relevant to the subject matter of written questions are available from 2013 to 2017.</p>

<p>Before the 2014-15 session, Lords written questions were made available after they received an answer in Hansard.</p>

<p>From the 2014-15 session, Lords written questions were made available before an answer was received, together with the names of answering bodies. Web locations for written questions which are yet to be answered were made available.</p>


<h2>Petitions and observations </h2>

<p>
Records with indexed references are available from the 1992-93 session.</p>

 <p>
Records with web links are available from December 2000. </p>

<p>
Records with full text are available from the 2005-06 session.</p>

<h2>Research briefings </h2>

<p>Records of POST publications are available from May 1989.</p>

<p>Records of Commons Library briefings are available from January 1993.</p>

<p>Records of Lords Library briefings are available from June 1998. </p>
